title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a Wayang Plan that take the cities in interesting_municipalities_cities textfile and returns all organisations which have a matching municipality in the textfile. The textfile only have cities, but a municipality is usually called something like the city. Output the result in a textfile.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val orgName = r.getField(3).toString; val muniOrig = r.getField(5).toString; val base = muniOrig.toLowerCase.trim.replaceAll("\\s*kommune\\s*$", "").trim; (base, (orgId, orgName, muniOrig)) }
(t: (String, (String, (Int, String, String)))) => { val org = t._2._2; s"${org._1} | ${org._2} | ${org._3}" }

log.thoughts: Load cities from the text file, normalize to lowercase; normalize organisation municipalities by stripping the 'kommune' suffix, then equi-join on the normalized names and output matching organisations to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, name, municipality FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val orgName = r.getField(3).toString; val muniOrig = r.getField(5).toString; val base = muniOrig.toLowerCase.trim.replaceAll("\\s*kommune\\s*$", "").trim; (base, (orgId, orgName, muniOrig)) }
(t: (String, (String, (Int, String, String)))) => { val org = t._2._2; s"${org._1} | ${org._2} | ${org._3}" }
